label: Brewery openings
title: Brewery openings
chatter: After Dayton in 2011 signed the 'Surly Bill,' which opened the door for brewers to serve beer on site, the number of craft breweries in the state exploded.

label: New business filings
title: New business filings
chatter: The number of new business filings in Minnesota each year has rebounded significantly after a post-recession slump.

label: Foreign-born population
title: Immigrant population
chatter: Minnesota's foreign-born population has continually increased over the years.
source: U.S. Census Bureau, Minnesota State Demographic Center

label: Public transportation use
title: Increasing hours in traffic
chatter: Public transportation ridership (in millions) gradually increased since the Pawlenty years.
source: Minnesota Department of Transportation, Metropolitan Council

label: Population of color
title: Population of color
chatter: Minnesota's population of color has steadily ticked upward.
source: U.S. Census Bureau, Minnesota State Demographic Center

label: Wolf population
title: Wolf population
chatter: Since the Minnesota Department of Natural Resources began conducting annual wolf population estimates in 2005, the number of wolves in the state has rebounded in the last few years after falling in the previous decade.
source: Minnesota Department of Natural Resources estimate

label: Education spending
title: Elementary and secondary education spending
chatter: State and local elementary and secondary education spending (in billions of 2017 dollars) has gradually increased.

label: Broadband access
title: Increasing broadband Internet access
chatter: The percentage of Minnesota households with access to high-speed broadband Internet has steadily increased due to efforts to improve connectivity across the state, including from the Governor's Task Force on Broadband.
source: Minnesota DEED, Connected Nation, Governor's Task Force on Broadband

label: State/local expenditures
title: State and local government expenditures
chatter: Minnesota state and local government expenditures (in billions of 2017 dollars) have steadily risen across administrations.

label: Median income
title: Median household income
chatter: Minnesota's median household income reached a low point following the Great Recession but has been rebounding since. Still, it remains lower than its peak during the Ventura administration.

label: U 4-year graduation rate
title: University of Minnesota four-year graduation rate
chatter: The University of Minnesota's four-year graduation rate has gradually improved over time.
source: University of Minnesota Office of Institutional Research

label: Walleye population
title: Mille Lacs walleye population
chatter: The walleye population of Lake Mille Lacs has been a hot political topic in Minnesota during Dayton's tenure. Minnesota's DNR has allowed catch-and-release fishing only for state-licensed anglers for the past three summers, to allow the walleye population to rebuild.
source: Minnesota Department of Natural Resources model estimate

label: Jobs
title: Jobs
chatter: The total number of nonfarm payroll jobs in Minnesota has gradually risen since the end of the Great Recession.

label: Snow/ice removal
title: Snow and ice removal
chatter: The percentage of Minnesota state highways cleared of snow and ice within the target time of three to 36 hours has increased in recent years.

label: Public health insurance
title: Public health insurance
chatter: The percentage of Minnesotans with health insurance through a public program has increased since the passage of the Affordable Care Act in 2010.

label: Renewable energy
title: Electricity generated from renewable resources
chatter: The percentage of Minnesota's energy coming from renewable resources has increased over the past decade.

label: Incarceration rate
title: Minnesota state prison incarceration rate
chatter: Minnesota's state prison incarceration rate per 100,000 residents has been rising steadily for years after a slight decrease near the beginning of Dayton's administration.

label: Traffic delay hours
title: Hours spent in traffic
chatter: The average number of hours spent by commuters in traffic each year was rising before stabilizing in the Pawlenty years, and has remained relatively flat under Dayton.
source: Texas A&M Transportation Institute, Urban Mobility Scorecard

label: Metro population
title: Metro population
chatter: The population of the Twin Cities metro area has steadily increased.
source: U.S. Census Bureau, Minnesota State Demographic Center

label: Graduation rate
title: High school graduation rate
chatter: Minnesota's overall high school graduation rate has gradually increased.

label: Math proficiency
title: Math proficiency
chatter: The percentage Minnesota eighth graders meeting state math standards has been relatively flat since 2011.

label: Adults working
title: Adults in workforce
chatter: The percentage of Minnesota adults aged 16 to 64 in the workforce gradually recovered to its pre-Great Recession level.

label: College degrees
title: Minnesotans with college degrees
chatter: The percentage of Minnesotans with a bachelor's degree or higher has increased slowly but steadily.

label: Freeway congestion
title: Freeway congestion
chatter: The percentage of congested freeway miles during peak times in the Twin Cities has gradually crept upward.

label: Obesity
title: Obesity
chatter: The percentage of Minnesotans older than 19 who are obese has gradually crept higher in recent years.
source: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention

label: Outstate population
title: Greater Minnesota population
chatter: Population growth in Greater Minnesota's rural and outstate areas has been more stagnant than the metro area in recent decades.
source: U.S. Census Bureau, Minnesota State Demographic Center

label: Open enrollment
title: Open enrollment
chatter: Since the introduction of open enrollment in Minnesota's schools back in 1993, the percentage of students attending schools outside their home district has gradually increased.

label: Median age
title: Median age
chatter: Minnesota's median age has slightly increased over the years.
source: U.S. Census Bureau, Minnesota State Demographic Center

label: Diabetes
title: Diabetes diagnoses
chatter: The percentage of Minnesotans older than 19 who are diagnosed with diabetes has remained relatively flat in recent years.
source: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention

label: Six-year graduation rate
title: College graduation rate
chatter: The percentage of students at Minnesota's colleges and universities who graduate within six years has gradually increased over time.

label: GDP
title: State gross domestic product
chatter: Minnesota's annual change in gross domestic product bounced back after the Great Recession but has stayed above zero since.

label: Reading proficiency
title: Reading proficiency
chatter: The percentage of Minnesota third graders meeting state reading standards has been relatively flat since 2013.

label: U enrollment
title: University of Minnesota enrollment
chatter: The University of Minnesota's fall semester enrollment has remained steady over time.
source: University of Minnesota Office of Institutional Research

label: Undergraduate loans
title: Undergraduate loans
chatter: The cumulative total of undergraduate student loans (in 2016 dollars) in Minnesota had been climbing steadily for years before declining toward the end of Pawlenty's administration and more or less flattening under Dayton.

label: U tuition
title: University of Minnesota tuition
chatter: In-state resident tuition (in 2018 dollars ) at the University of Minnesota had been increasing steadily until a tuition freeze deal with the Legislature in 2013.
source: University of Minnesota Office of Institutional Research

label: Volunteerism
title: Declines in volunteerism
chatter: The percentage of Minnesotans aged 16 or older who volunteered in the past year has gradually declined.
source: U.S. Census Bureau, Minnesota State Demographic Center

label: Poverty
title: Poverty
chatter: The percentage of Minnesotans in poverty has ticked down slightly after the Great Recession.

label: Greenhouse emissions
title: Greenhouse emissions reductions
chatter: As measured in tons, greenhouse gas emissions have remained more or less flat since 2011.

label: Disabled elderly
title: Elderly Minnesotans with disabilities
chatter: The percentage of Minnesotans aged 65 or older with a disability has remained relatively flat.

label: Homeownership gap
title: Homeownership gap
chatter: The homeownership gap, the percent difference between white residents and those of color who own homes, increased during the Great Recession before leveling off.

label: Traffic casualties
title: Traffic injuries and fatalities
chatter: The rate of traffic injuries and fatalities per 100,000 residents has declined in Minnesota over the past couple decades.
source: Minnesota Department of Public Safety, National Highway Traffic Safety Administration, U.S. Census Bureau

label: Traffic over bad bridges
title: Traffic over deficient bridges
chatter: The percentage of urban traffic traveling over structurally deficient bridges in Minnesota has decreased significantly since the 2007 collapse of the 35W Bridge.

label: Unemployment rate
title: Unemployment
chatter: Minnesota's unemployment rate has declined drastically since the end of the Great Recession.

label: Poor highways
title: Fewer miles of poor highways
chatter: The percentage of highways rated as having poor ride quality by MNDOT has gradually decreased.

label: Homelessness
title: Increases in homelessness
chatter: The number of Minnesotans experiencing homelessness increased over the years, but has seen a slight decline recently.

label: Deficient bridges
title: Fewer deficient bridges
chatter: The percentage of Minnesota bridges that are structurally deficient decreased significantly since the collapse of the 35W Bridge in 2007.

label: White unemployment
title: White unemployment
chatter: Unemployment rates among Minnesota's white population has decreased significantly since the end of the Great Recession.

label: Health uninsurance rate
title: Health uninsurance rate
chatter: The percentage of Minnesotans without health insurance has dropped by half since the enaction of the federal Affordable Care Act in 2010.

label: Congested lane miles
title: Less traffic congestion
chatter: The percentage of Twin Cities lane miles congested during rush hour has slightly decreased over time.
source: Texas A&M Transportation Institute, Urban Mobility Scorecard

label: State/local revenue
title: State and local government revenue
chatter: Minnesota's state and local government revenue (in billions of 2017 dollars) dipped during the Pawlenty years before rising again under Dayton.

label: Hispanic unemployment
title: Hispanic unemployment
chatter: Unemployment rates among Minnesota's Hispanic population has decreased significantly since the end of the Great Recession.

label: Mississippi nitrates
title: Nitrate pollution in the Mississippi River
chatter: Nitrate contamination, often from chemical fertilizers and manure used in agriculture, as well as sewage, is a principal contributor to algae growth in lakes and rivers. Nitrate levels in the Mississippi River have increased in recent years, according to five-year averages as measured in metric tons at Lock and Dam #3 near Red Wing.

label: Cost-burdened housing
title: Cost-burdened housing
chatter: The share of cost-burdened Minnesota households paying 30 percent or more of their income on housing costs gradually climbed during the Pawlenty administration before declining under Dayton.

label: Mental health admissions
title: Mental health admissions
chatter: The rate of psychiatric hospital admissions per 1,000 Minnesotans aged older than 13 has remained relatively flat over the years.
source: Minnesota Hospital Association, National Center for Health Statistics

label: Crime rate
title: Crime rate
chatter: Mirroring national trends, Minnesota's statewide uniform crime rate per 100,000 residents, which includes violent and property crimes, has fallen steadily over the past two decades.

label: Mississippi phosphorus
title: Phosphorus pollution in the Mississippi River
chatter: Phosphorus pollution, a major contributor to algae growth in lakes and rivers, has ebbed and flowed in the Mississippi River, according to five-year averages as measured in metric tons at Lock and Dam #3 near Red Wing.

label: Black unemployment
title: Black unemployment
chatter: Unemployment rates among Minnesota's black population has decreased significantly since the end of the Great Recession, but remains more than twice that of white Minnesotans.

label: Moose population
title: Moose population
chatter: Minnesota's moose population stabilized somewhat after a decade-long decline, but shows no signs of recovery, according to the Minnesota DNR's aerial moose survey, which has been conducted annually in northeastern Minnesota since 2013.
source: Minnesota Department of Natural Resources aerial survey
